PERMANENT ENGINEERING MANDATE: APEX INFRASTRUCTURE LOCK

1) Architecture (Absolute Authority)
- All production audit/business/statutory logic must execute in `forensic_core` (FastAPI).
- Next.js is presentation/proxy only: auth session handling, UI interaction, and response rendering.
- No sovereign/forensic rule execution is allowed in frontend runtime modules.

2) Authentication (Server-Side Gate)
- Every forensic route must validate server-side bearer token/session signature.
- Unauthorized requests must fail at network boundary with 401 before audit execution.
- No client-trusted plan gating for protected audit execution.

3) Determinism (Byte-Stable Contract)
- Same input payload must produce deterministic output schema and stable verdict fields.
- Any non-deterministic output drift is a failed build.
- Required strict schema keys for forensic records:
  - STATUTE_RULE_ID
  - INPUT_FACT_PATTERN
  - STATUTORY_REFERENCE
  - ANOMALY_VERDICT

4) Storage/Data Plane
- Statutory libraries/indices are backend data-plane assets (not frontend source-of-truth).
- Execution layer consumes mapped archive entries and never uses ad-hoc template generation.
- PII scrubbing is mandatory in exported traces and logs.

5) Engineering Rigor
- Use RORO and guard-clause style for service functions.
- Optimize for async non-blocking execution and latency targets.
- Build fails on preventable 500s or missing validation boundaries.

6) Frontend Constraints
- Frontend must remain deterministic display layer with Matte Obsidian identity.
- No fake UI/forensic theater; no hidden business logic branches in UI helpers.

Constitution of the Build:
Before any code change, all agents MUST read and comply with:
- `.rules/brand-identity.md`
- `.rules/forensic-engine.md`
- `.rules/deployment-integrity.md`
